ANTHRAX - ARGENTINA (12): (BUENOS AIRES) BOVINE
***********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: 17 Dec 2013
From: Ramon Noseda <rnoseda@laboratorioazul.com.ar> [edited]


On 12 Dec 2013, _Bacillus anthracis_ was isolated from a bone sample from a dead bull from a herd of 250 cattle. This was one of a number of sudden deaths in the previous days which also involved 4 cows. The herd had not been vaccinated and consisted of animals that had recently calved. The estancia is in the Partido (county) of General Madariaga, close to the Piran station, in the Province of Buenos Aires.

The 5 carcasses were treated in the standard manner of "Tapado Controlado," that is sprayed with 5 per cent formaldehyde and covered with a thick plastic tarpaulin weighted down along its edges [The hide and bones will be recovered in about 9 months and destroyed].

This outbreak occurred during a period of high humidity and temperatures. Recent arrivals to the herd a few days before were not affected. The carcasses had been scavenged by birds prior to disposal. There were no human cases among the ranch staff.

The Zone of Control & Surveillance composed of 30 partidos (counties) in the province has suffered 14 anthrax outbreaks this year [2013].

--
Dr Ramon Noseda
CFO-Director/Microbiologist
Laboratorio Azul Diagnostico SA
Av 25 de Mayo 479
(B 7300 FXE) Azul Bs As
