[Our thanks to Ramon for this prompt and reliable report.

This partida is on the far eastern margin of Buenos Aires Province. Anthrax outbreaks are usually in the central body of the province to the west of this outbreak. As there is plenty of grazing at this time of year (essentially mid-summer), the source is, therefore, probably from spores in an old cattle grave that have been brought to the surface by the rains, and the flat nature of the area, to be then grazed.

For a map of Argentina, go to:
http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/americas/argentina_rel96.jpg.
For General Madariaga, go to:
http://www.fallingrain.com/world/AR/01/General_Juan_Madariaga.html. - Mod.MHJ

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/1yJb.]
